Denmark and Inter Milan player Christian Eriksen has left the football fraternity in great shock. This after the former Tottenham Hotspur playmaker collapsed on the pitch in Saturday's Euro 2020 game against Finland in Copenhagen. The match was suspended in the first half. Eriksen was taken off on a stretcher after needing medical attention for about 10 minutes. His teammates were in tears as medical staff tried to revive the 29-year-old. "The UEFA EURO 2020 match in Copenhagen has been suspended due to a medical emergency," UEFA said in a short statement. The fans in the stadium, who were enjoying a rare chance to watch their team in action again, were left in shock. They will, however be pleased to learn that Eriksen has been stabilized in hospital. “Following the medical emergency involving Denmark’s player Christian Eriksen, a crisis meeting has taken place with both teams and match officials and further information will be communicated at 19:45 CET“The player has been transferred to the hospital and has been stabilized,” read a tweet from UEFA. Following the medical emergency involving Denmark’s player Christian Eriksen, a crisis meeting has taken place with both teams and match officials and further information will be communicated at 19:45 CET. The player has been transferred to the hospital and has been stabilised. 